data.title: Senior General Than Shwe sees off Prime Minister - Online Burma ...

data.text: Established 1914 Volume XVII, Number 45 8th Waxing of Nayon 1371 ME Sunday, 31 May, 2009 Senior General Than Shwe sees off Prime Minister General Thein Sein on departure for Republic of Korea NAY PYI TAW, 30 May — Chairman of the State Peace and Development Council Commander-in-Chief of Defence Services Senior General Than Shwe saw off Prime Minister General Thein Sein at Nay Pyi Taw Airport at 4 p.m today on the Prime Minister’s departure for the Republic of Korea to attend the ASEAN- Korea Commemorative Summit and Related Summits of Bilateral Summit and ASEAN- ROK CEO Summit to be held in Jeju Island at the invitation of Mr Lee Myung-bak, President of the Republic of Korea. Together with the Senior General, who saw off the Prime Minister, were Vice- Chairman of the State Peace and Development Council Deputy Commanderin-Chief of Defence Chairman of the State Peace and Development Council Commander-in-Chief of Defence Services Senior General Than Shwe shakes hands with Prime Minister General Thein Sein at Nay Pyi Taw Airport. MNA Four political objectives * Stability of the State, community peace and tranquillity, prevalence of law and order * National reconsolidation * Emergence of a new enduring State Constitution * Building of a new modern developed nation in accord with the new State Constitution Chairman of the State Peace and Development Council Commander-in-Chief of Defence Services Senior General Than Shwe sees off Prime Minister General Thein Sein at Nay Pyi Taw Airport.—MNA Services Commanderin-Chief (Army) Vice- Senior General Maung Aye, member of the State Peace and Development Council General Thura Shwe Mann of the Ministry of Defence, Secretary-1 of the State Peace and Development Council General Thiha Thura Tin Aung Myint Oo, SPDC member Lt-Gen Tin Aye of the Ministry of Defence, Commanderin-Chief (Navy) Rear- Admiral Nyan Tun, Four economic objectives * Development of agriculture as the base and all-round development of other sectors of the economy as well * Proper evolution of the market-oriented economic system * Development of the economy inviting participation in terms of technical know-how and investments from sources inside the country and abroad * The initiative to shape the national economy must be kept in the hands of the State and the national peoples 31-5-09 NL 1 18/7/29, 4:43 PM Commander-in-Chief (Air) Lt-Gen Myat Hein, Adjutant-General Lt-Gen Thura Myint Aung, Lt-Gen Ye Myint of the Ministry of Defence, Commander of Nay Pyi Taw Command Maj-Gen Wai Lwin, Deputy Minister for Transport Col Nyan Tun Aung, the Director-General of the SPDC Office and heads of department, Charge d’ Affaires ai of the Embassy of the Republic of Korea to Myanmar Mr Chung In- Gyun and officials. The Prime Minister-led delegation comprises Minister for Foreign Affairs U Nyan Win, the Director General of the Government Office and departmental heads. Minister for National Planning and Economic Development U Soe Tha, who is also a member of the delegation, left for ROK on 27 May in advance. MNA Four social objectives * Uplift of the morale and morality of the entire nation * Uplift of national prestige and integrity and preservation and safeguarding of cultural heritage and national character * Uplift of dynamism of patriotic spirit * Uplift of health, fitness and education standards of the entire nation
